{"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"nonisolated","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"geometryGroup","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","text":"View","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"\n","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default OpenSwiftUI views push position and size changes down"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"through the view hierarchy, so that only views that draw"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"something (known as leaf views) apply the current animation to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"their frame rectangle. However in some cases this coalescing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"behavior can give undesirable results; inserting a geometry"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"group can correct that. A group acts as a barrier between the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parent view and its subviews, forcing the position and size"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"values to be resolved and animated by the parent, before being"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"passed down to each subview."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The example below shows one use of this function: ensuring that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the member views of each row in the stack apply (and animate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as) a single geometric transform from their ancestor view,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"rather than letting the effects of the ancestor views be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"applied separately to each leaf view. If the members of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ItemView"},{"text":" may be added and removed at different times the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"group ensures that they stay locked together as animations are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"applied.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["VStack {","    ForEach(items) { item in","        ItemView(item: item)","            .geometryGroup()","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Returns: a new view whose geometry is isolated from that of its","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"parent view.","type":"text"}]}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Isolates the geometry (e.g. position and size) of the view"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from its parent view."}],"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ModifiedContent"]]},"metadata":{"platforms":[{"introducedAt":"13.0","unavailable":false,"name":"iOS","deprecated":false,"beta":false},{"introducedAt":"10.15","unavailable":false,"name":"macOS","deprecated":false,"beta":false},{"introducedAt":"13.0","unavailable":false,"name":"tvOS","deprecated":false,"beta":false},{"introducedAt":"1.0","unavailable":false,"name":"visionOS","deprecated":false,"beta":false},{"introducedAt":"6.0","unavailable":false,"name":"watchOS","deprecated":false,"beta":false}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","modules":[{"relatedModules":["OpenSwiftUICore"],"name":"OpenSwiftUI"}],"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"method","extendedModule":"OpenSwiftUICore","externalID":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewPAAE13geometryGroupQryF::SYNTHESIZED: